question: Use UniProt clusters to find the similar proteins for UniProtKB entry P05067 and then sort them by UniRef cluster identity
expected_sparql:
SELECT 
    ?similar ?identity
FROM <http://sparql.uniprot.org/uniref>
FROM <http://sparql.uniprot.org/uniprot>
WHERE
{
    BIND (uniprotkb:P05607 AS ?protein)
    ?cluster up:member ?member ;
             up:member/up:sequenceFor ?protein;
             up:identity ?identity .
    ?member up:sequenceFor ?similar .
    FILTER(!sameTerm(?similar, ?protein))
} 
ORDER BY DESC(?identity)
improved_sparql:
SELECT DISTINCT 
  ?protein 
  ?identity
WHERE {
  <http://purl.uniprot.org/uniprot/P05067> ^up:member ?cluster .
  ?cluster up:member/up:sequenceFor ?protein .
  VALUES (?cluster ?identity) {
    (<http://purl.uniprot.org/uniref/UniRef100> 1.00)
    (<http://purl.uniprot.org/uniref/UniRef90> 0.90)
    (<http://purl.uniprot.org/uniref/UniRef50> 0.50)
  }
  FILTER(?protein != <http://purl.uniprot.org/uniprot/P05067>)
}
ORDER BY DESC(?identity)

  VALUES (?cluster ?identity) {

    (<http://purl.uniprot.org/uniref/UniRef90> 0.90)

}
